   senses:"Darkvision 120 ft.; Passive Perception 12",
   languages:"Common plus one other language",
   desc:"From a distance, will-o'-wisps look like lanterns bobbing in the dark. Through windows of abandoned structures or around bends of treacherous paths, they tempt the curious into peril. Once their prey is vulnerable, they feed on the life force of those they lay low.",
   traits:"Ephemeral. The wisp can't wear or carry anything.\nIncorporeal Movement. The wisp can move through other creatures and objects as if they were Difficult Terrain. It takes 5 (1d10) Force damage if it ends its turn inside an object.",
   actions:"Shock. Melee Attack Roll: +4, reach 5 ft. Hit: 11 (2d8+2) Lightning damage.",
